SIMPLE: topknot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topknot
<hw>Top"knot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A crest
or knot of feathers upon the head or top, as of a bird; also, an
ornamental knot worn on top of the head, as by women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A great, stout servant girl, with cheeks as red as her
<qex>topknot</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small Europen flounder
(<spn>Rhoumbus punctatus</spn>). The name is also applied to allied
species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topless</ent>⟦br⟧
